  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6589.75 sitting just below the massive +8.2B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to sell any push higher into that level, creating strong resistance. The PIN regime with 1B+ total GEX suggests dealers will actively fade moves - selling the 6605-6610 zone and buying any dip toward the 6500 negative gamma support level. The recent GEX surge indicates increased option flow is amplifying these hedging dynamics, making the 6500-6605 range a high-conviction trading zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6500-6605 with dealers capping upside and defending downside.",
